                INTRODUCTION

TinyCalc is a tiny spread sheet program
inspired by VisiCalc. It is provided
with the cc65 system as an example.

Since TinyCalc is only a demonstration
program it has its limitations:

  * You can not copy formulas.
  * You can not insert/delete lines.

In spite of its limitations TinyCalc
does provide some interesting features:

  *  Floating point reals (cc65)
  *  Mathematical functions (SIN, COS,
     LN, EXP etc.)
  *  Built in line editor for text
     and formula editing.
  *  Text can be entered across cells.
  *  Formula protection.
.PA
In addition to this TinyCalc offers
the usual features of a spread sheet:

  *  Load a spread sheet from disk.
  *  Save a spread sheet to disk.
  *  Automatic recalculation.
  *  Print the spread sheet.
  *  Clear the current spread sheet.

The spread sheet is an electronic
piece of paper for text, numbers
and formulas.

The next page shows the grid.
.PA
--------------------------------------
       A          B         C
 1   22.00
 2    1.00
 3    2.00
 4    3.00
 5   28.00
 .
 .
A 5  Formula: (A1+A2+A3+A4)
--------------------------------------

In the example cell A5 contains a
formula: (A1+A2+A3+A4) which means
the numbers in A1-A4 are added.

The formula can be abbreviated to:
(A1>A4) meaning: add all cells
from A1 to A4.
.PA
You move the cursor using the
CRSR keys:

           [CRSR UP]
    [CRSR LEFT]  [CRSR RIGHT]
          [CRSR DOWN]

A cell may contain a number,
a formula or some text. The type
and coordinates are shown in the
bottom corner:

A 5   Formula: (Cell A5 has formula)

A 1   Text    (Cell A1 has text)

A 2   Numeric (Cell A2 has a number)

.PA
               Summary
     Cells are denoted A1 through
     G21 (total 147 cells).

Functions and operators:
ABS, SQRT, SQR, SIN, COS, ARCTAN,
LN, LOG, EXP, FACT
+,-,*,/, ^ (power)
> denotes a range of cells.

Entering data
Move to cell and enter data.
TinyCalc determines if it is
numeric or text.

Navigation:
Use CRSR keys to move.

Field editing:
CRSR Left/Right moves in line.
INST/DEL deletes characters.
CLR/HOME moves to start/end.
RETURN finishes entry.
ESC (or <-) cancels changes.
.PA
              Commands

    /   restore screen
    Q   Quit TinyCalc
    L   Load from disk
    S   Save to disk
    R   Recalculate
    P   Print
    F   Change format
    A   AutoCalc ON/OFF

Note: use F command and enter -1
      for scientific notation.

.PA
              EXAMPLES

Valid cell formulas:

(A1+(B2-C7))  subtract C7 from B2,
              and add result to A1
(A1>A23)      sum of A1..A23
(A1>B5)       sum of A1..A5 and B1..B5

Complex formulas:

(SIN(A1)*COS(A2)/((1.2*A8)+
LN(FACT(A8)+8.9E-3))+(C1>C5))

To edit a cell, move to it and
press ESC (or <-), change and
press RETURN. Press ESC again
to restore old value.

